<br>
Let me first explain that my guild is a decent raiding guild. Our average raid force is a little over 50 people. We've taken down TT, HP, Cursed Cycle, Behemoth, VZ, etc etc with mid 40s. Yet, Aerin'Dar is the one fight we cannot seem to beat. We can get him to 10-15%, but the fact is that you can't keep a MA up against him. Three procs in a row and Furor would be dead without a CH chain that was faster than is humanly possible.<br>
<br>
WHAT THE @#%$ DID THEY DO THAT FOR? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I mean there's no point to making an encounter that's pure Zerg... I thought they *disliked* zerg.<br>
<br>
My advice:<br>
<br>
Take Aerin's proc, remove it.<br>
<br>
Change his AE to max range (ie to the wall) in the direction he's facing. Make the AE a 3kdd + 6 second stun and 20% slow. Basically, if he faces your raid and AE's, you're @#%$. Make him rampage about the same as HP, therefore requiring 3 - 4 healers to keep up a RT.<br>
<br>
/sigh... <p>Draogan -- 61 Archmage<br>
