<br>
terris thule, if you had one good solid tank for her and some good kiters, yes you could probably just shove your way through that, but it does take some strats.<br>
<br>
aerin`dar, behemoth, grummus, these are pure zerg.  you need almost no talent for these.  if you gathered up like 50 nukers and another 50 melees...the melees would hold aggro just by low-HP as they died, allowing the nukers to cast about 3 or 4 spells each and zap, dead dragon.<br>
<br>
-------<br>
anyway, a good practical aerin`dar strat...<br>
<br>
positioning:  i remember one time through this fight, where using firebolt i was far enough back that i never took an AE hit.  casters don't have to take the AE, most of them anyway.<br>
<br>
resists:  the fear/dot IS resistable...it's just really hard to.  if you can get up to like a 400 resist you're pretty safe from it.  that means bards, and a decent number of them.<br>
<br>
i'm not 100% sure on the tanking issue.  i'm assuming you had it crippled to kill the proc rate, but he still procs a good amount which can screw you up.  can't remember the name of the proc spell offhand, but i think it may be resistable as well.  key may be getting MT to like 500MR and clerics on him to 400+<br>
<br>
