 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lordgojirax>LordGojirax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 446<br> <font color=#333333>(2/10/03 4:46:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=423.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.jackntracie.com/images/gojhead.jpg width=98 height=126></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_smile.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: ..</span><hr size=1> Killed Aerin’Dar last night after 4 failed attempts in a two day campaign against him.<br>
<br>
The biggest thing in a fight like this is to NOT lose heart!<br>
<br>
It takes HUGE numbers…<br>
<br>
We tried CH Chains. (I setup the Chain and tried a number of tactics.) We tried a bunch of things. Here’s what worked for us.<br>
<br>
Clerics spam supernal remedy (This allows them to heal the main tank and turn a quick heal on themselves as needed.) Worked fine. Also, the SECOND you see that “Glass Roar” DOT land on you have your Priest classes hit Radiant Cure. (Radiant Cure 1 is enough to remove the DOT.) Otherwise they are taking 600 damage per tick from that as well.<br>
<br>
Setup Enchanter/Necromancer teams. We setup 4 such teams. 2 on each side of Aerin’Dars platform.  As the golems become active, the Chanters tash and the Necros rooted em.  Worked like a charm and kept them out of the fight until long after the dragon was dead. (We even rooted a named Golem out of the way.)<br>
<br>
For Aerin’Dar you definitely go ALL DAMAGE balls to the wall blasting. Rangers use trueshot on inc, warriors go damage. Main tank (And SA/TA etc.) uses Auto-Riposte discipline instead of Defensive. This stops the dragon from landing melee hits which in turn stops that nasty proc from going off.<br>
<br>
The Dragon was very soft to Magic as well. Not sure about other types, but Magic landed real well.<br>
<br>
We also had a person dedicated to timing the AoE and called out when there was 10 seconds to go before the AoE went off. That allowed the casters to back out of range, then move back in to blast.<br>
<br>
All in all the fight lasts barely over 60 seconds. We had 82 people in our raid btw.<br>
<br>
Boy were they surprised in Halls of Honor when the 80+ of us zoned in. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
